table.name: monthly_population_vic
table.Comment: Population growth in Victoria per month. From now data covers 1902/12/01 until 2005/01/01. Need to complete data until 2019.

table.name: cpi_conversion
table.Comment: Data to correct prices using CPI. From 1901 to 1965 in pre-decimal and 1966 onwards in decimal system, corrected at 2018 prices.

table.name: domestic_consumers
table.Comment: Number of domestic consumers per year. The total of domestic consumers is given at the last month of each year e.g. 1935-12-01.

table.name: generation_demand_historic
table.Comment: Merge of generation data from open NEM, Demand data VIC and SECV data

table.name: solar_exposure_monthly
table.Comment: Monthly mean daily global solar exposure (MJ/m*m) http://www.bom.gov.au/ Data for the Melbourne Olympic Park station

table.name: solar_installation_monthly
table.Comment: Includes average installation of solar pv by size per month from https://pv-map.apvi.org.au/analyses

table.name: tariffdata
table.Comment: Includes the tariffs for the 4 case study areas from 1900 to 1990

table.name: totaldemandvictoria
table.Comment: Total Demand in Victoria from Dec 1998 to Jul 2019 each 30 minutes. Demand is in MW. Downloaded from https://www.aemo.com.au/Electricity/National-Electricity-Market-NEM/Data-dashboard#aggregated-data

column.name: date
column.Comment: Date in yyyy-mm-dd format.

column.name: date
column.Comment: annual data.

column.name: solar_roofpv_dollargwh
column.Comment: Market value $/GWh

column.name: product_code
column.Comment: Product code from the BoM climate data

column.name: station_number
column.Comment: station number. E.g. 86338 for Olympic Park

column.name: solar_exposure
column.Comment: Monthly mean daily global solar exposure (MJ/m*m)

column.name: id
column.Comment: Id of tariff. Has two components, the year in YYYY format and the id which is an integer number. For instance, a tariff id for year 1900 can be 19001, or for 1983 will be 19831.

column.name: casestudy_area
column.Comment: The case study areas are the same, however the boundaries might have changed over time. M1 corresponds to any site within Melbourne City Council M2: Any site of inner suburbs, inner melbourne, or Metropolitan area R1: Ballarat R2: Wodonga/Yackandandah

column.name: date
column.Comment: Year the tariff was active for each case study area.

column.name: tariff_name
column.Comment: The name of the tariff. Might correspond to an organisation name, but it is not always the case.

column.name: firstxunits_dkwh
column.Comment: This tariff corresponds to the description of rates from 1900 to 1905. It is given in pre-decimal system. The x corresponds to 20 units in this case and the demand was mostly public lighting, commercial and few industries.

column.name: afterxunits_dkwh
column.Comment: This tariff corresponds to the description of rates from 1900 to 1905. It is given in pre-decimal system. The x corresponds to 20 units in this case and the demand was mostly public lighting, commercial and few industries.

column.name: lightflat_dkwh
column.Comment: Light flat rate in pre-decimal system.

column.name: powerflat_dkwh
column.Comment: Power flat rate in pre-decimal system.

column.name: lightmaxdemand_dkwh
column.Comment: Lighting charges for maximum demand in pre-decimal system.

column.name: powermaxdemand_dkwh
column.Comment: Power charges for maximum demand in pre-decimal system.

column.name: lightfirstxunits_dkwh
column.Comment: Light charges first x units in pre-decimal system. X in 1906 corresponded to 1000 units.

column.name: lightsecondxunits_dkwh
column.Comment: Light charges second x units in pre-decimal system. X in 1906 corresponded to 1000 units.

column.name: lightthirdxunits_dkwh
column.Comment: Light charges third x units in pre-decimal system. X in 1906 corresponded to 1000 units.

column.name: lightthereafter_dkwh
column.Comment: Light charges after second x units in pre-decimal system. X in 1906 corresponded to over 3000 units.

column.name: powerandheat_dkwh
column.Comment: Power and heat started being charged separatly from 1907.

column.name: powerandheatxhourspeak_dkwh
column.Comment: Power and heat first x hours peak in pre-decimal system. In 1909 x was 75.

column.name: poweandheatoverxhourspeak_dkwh
column.Comment: Power and heat after x hours peak in pre-decimal system. In 1909 x was 75.

column.name: chargeperroom_dmonth
column.Comment: Service charge per room per month in pre-decimal system.

column.name: threeroomsgbgdgrfirstx_ckwhquarter
column.Comment: Residential 3 rooms or less "GB"/"GD"/"GR" First X units per quarter starts in 1971. X varies with time. The charge is in decimal system. The G, GB, GD and GR tariffs are included in this column depending on the year.

column.name: threeroomsgbgdgrnextx_ckwhquarter
column.Comment: Residential 3 rooms or less "GB"/"GD"/"GR" Next X units per quarter starts in 1971. X varies with time. The charge is in decimal system. The G, GB, GD and GR tariffs are included in this column depending on the year.

column.name: threeroomsgbgdgrbalance_ckwhquarter
column.Comment: Residential 3 rooms or less "GB"/"GD"/"GR" balance X units per quarter starts in 1971. X varies with time. The charge is in decimal system. The G, GB, GD and GR tariffs are included in this column depending on the year.

column.name: jfirstx_ckwhquarter
column.Comment: J tariff in decimal system. The x represents 1200kwh per quarter in 1969.

column.name: jbalance_ckwhquarter
column.Comment: J tariff in decimal system. The balance of the J tariff from SECV.

column.name: secvij_gdgr_aud_quarter
column.Comment: SECV tariffs I&J (space and water heating) and residential GD and GR. Charges are in dollars per quarter.

column.name: jy_aud_quarter
column.Comment: Water and space heating tariffs Y and J starting in 1984. Charges are in dollars per quarter.

column.name: energycharge_cdkwh
column.Comment: Tariff energy in d/unit or c/kWh. Sometimes coincide with the average price per tariff. It might be given in pre-decimal or decimal system. Fix rates are not included.

column.name: standingcharge_aud_year
column.Comment: Standing charge in $ per year. Usual fix rate charged currently by NSP and Retailers.

column.Comment: Transmission and distribution tariffs from AusNet.

column.Comment: Transmission and distribution tariffs from AusNet.

column.Comment: Transmission and distribution tariffs from AusNet.

column.name: tuosaverage_ckwh
column.Comment: Transmission and distribution tariffs from AusNet.

column.Comment: Transmission and distribution tariffs from AusNet.

column.Comment: Transmission and distribution tariffs from AusNet.

column.name: networksummerpeak
column.Comment: Transmission and distribution tariffs from AusNet.

column.name: networksummershouder_ckwh
column.Comment: Transmission and distribution tariffs from AusNet.

column.Comment: Transmission and distribution tariffs from AusNet.

column.name: networkaverage_ckwh
column.Comment: Transmission and distribution tariffs from AusNet.

column.name: extrasummerexport_ckwh
column.Comment: Transmission and distribution tariffs from AusNet.

column.name: premiumfit_ckwh
column.Comment: Transmission and distribution tariffs from AusNet.Premium feed in tariff.

column.name: jurisdictional_ckwh
column.Comment: Transmission and distribution tariffs from AusNet.Jurisdictional charges.

column.name: average_dckwh
column.Comment: Average price in pre-decimal or decimal system. d/unit or c/KWh.
